[It is not entirely clear whether the fatality is the 9 year old girl mentioned in the post below. - Mod.LL]

******
[2]
Date: Wed 12 Aug 2015
Source: WSBT [edited]
http://www.wsbt.com/news/local/e-coli-concerns-center-around-local-day-care/34672716


Families want answers after 2 confirmed cases of _E. coli_ [O157] surfaced in several Indiana counties. Now, the department is looking into 3 other suspected cases.

Investigators initially pointed to a local day care, but the state is looking at other possibilities. The investigation comes on the heels of [the death last week of a] 9 year old girl from Rochester. Family members say she died from _E. coli_ and she didn't go to a day care. The State Department of Health says they're investigating reports of a death, but it's too early to say she died from the bacterium.

A couple dozen people came to the Rochester courthouse advocating change -- including the family of 3 year old twins who spent weeks at Riley Hospital for Children. Doctors told them they [had] got _E. coli_ from something they ate. The boys didn't go to a day care either. The family says they don't want this to happen to anyone else.

Again, the State Department of Health says it's too early to tell if the 9 year old died from _E. coli_. At this point, it's just the 2 confirmed cases -- 1 in Fulton County and 1 in Wabash County. There is no official word on where the 3 suspected cases are located.

